  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is examine the relationship between adipose tissue inflammation and
      activation of the endocannabinoid system before and after Roux-en-Y gastric bypass surgery.
      The investigators hypothesize that the metabolic improvements and weight loss are due to
      mechanisms that antagonize the endocannabinoid system.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
